items.name: PhoenixMix
items.description:
Color coded in red is highly recommended

Color coded in yellow is clearly unsure

Color coded in lime green is optional

Sorry I’m late; I was a bit too lazy/nervous to upload if.

Description

So, Basically, this model is a checkpoint merge of the following models:

  • s6yx's Rev Animated

  • Merjic's majicMIX realistic

  • Cyberdelia's CyberRealistic (classic)

  • Epinikion's epiCRealism

  • XpucT's Deliberate

  • More checkpoints to be merged in later versions if you suggest me one because I'll try my best to train my models to look better due to my disability and my potato devices

If these links don’t work, please let me know

All models above belongs to their respective owners/creators, not me (I'm the one crediting them)

Tips

As I said [due to my disability and my low-end device], these are the tips I could give you so far:

  • I don’t know what VAE to use, so please let me know in the comments

  • If your image looks weird or abnormal than what you expected, then you may need to add these to the prompt: i.e. ((best quality)), ((masterpiece)), (detailed) from Rev's; ((8k resolution)), ultradetailed, (perfect quality), highest quality, ((perfect proportion)); fine details.

  • For the negative prompt: i.e. ((worst quality, blurry, watermark, noise, noisy, pixelated, corrupted, glitched, too much contrast, now enough contrast, imbalanced quality)).

  • If your character looks ugly and have messy body parts, you may need to put the prompts like: (((perfect proportion, perfect anatomy, perfect face, perfect eyes, perfect nose, perfect mouth, perfect hands, all 5 fingers, perfect feet, all 5 toes, even body parts))). Unfortunately, I do not know the order/strength so you may need to figure it out :(

  • The negative prompt is basically an opposite of what is above (the third point in tips): i.e. (((worst proportion, worst anatomy, worst face, worst eyes, worst nose, worst mouth, worst hands, missing fingers, more than 5 fingers, worst feet, missing toes, uneven body parts)))

  • The best negative textual inversion to use is <ng_deepnegative_v1_75t> (https://civitai.com/models/4629/deep-negative-v1x) I couldn’t convert it to link for some reason

  • Use the line break if they offer one

  • The best image size depends

  • If your device runs perfectly or can handle things "without burning", then these are following upscalers you can use: Remacri, Universal Upscaler V2 Sharp, Real-Esrgan X2+ (for low ends who wants the best quality)

  • Depending on your device, use steps ranged from 25-45

  • Text guidance should be from 5-7

  • Take the lowest clip skip as possible

  • request me some tips to use this model so I can change them asap

  • Also, sorry for me grammar/spelling, especially when writing on a phone (oof, uncomfortable)

Features

Pros

  • The text input has freedom/unrestricted, making it pretty flexible

  • Most of the time, the model creates well-made quality so I don’t want to get further into this.

  • They did a decent job on poses

  • Easy to generate women and non-binary folks (what I meant is androgynous).

Mehs

  • Loras seem to work but certain prompts, especially related to centaurs, Have a few change to work. Maybe adding enough strength works

Cons

  • Even with negative prompts, the hands and faces seemed off

  • Doesn’t really work great with low ends

  • Inpainting/tiles/refining is difficult to do

  • It can get sexist because when you prompts (such as "man wearing a dress and skirt"), it generates a woman instead of a man. If you want a man instead, then you should strengthen it and put woman/women/female/girls in the negative prompt with enough strength (what I’m saying is by using parentheses).

Origins/Fun Facts

  • This model was originally used to make an unreleased model with the longest name ever, but my phone couldn’t handle it

  • I named this model [PhoenixMix] because Phoenixes are my favorite mythical birds/creatures (besides mermaids). My apology for the bias.

  • This is the first uploaded model I created

Disclaimer

  • if you want to merge this model, then you should definitely credit me. Every time I see merged models/or used ones, only a few credit someone for using it. =(

  • If you generate an image, please provide everything (such as positive/negative prompts, steps, cfg, and models) so I can gain more influence.

  • Do not sell anything (i.e. models and images) that revolves around PhoenixMix, because it fan cause conflicts with an NFT (very controversial) and I don’t like to get into conflicts with anything like those.

  • Again, sorry about the spelling/grammar (although my english seems to be great)

  • Again, comment me if you suggest me

items.name: Light painting photography | Flowing light, color and shape move freely
items.description:
The model is used to provide an effect similar to light-painting photography for the generated image, (mainly characters, in the non-realistic model, mechs and vehicles seem to have good effects). The realistic model is a bit like the one released by social platforms ( Can you try to generate some to remove the camouflage?), there is a certain degree of reduction. In 2d and 2.5d models, the generated light will be more and more like a magic effect. Take what you need for your use case.

Suggestions for generation: I used Moyou, mjmix, reV, and awpainting to generate the examples. Mecha and underwater have been used in conjunction with my other lora. The specific parameters can be seen in the image generation data. High-definition restoration is required. The generation weight is recommended to be 0.7 Between -0.9, if it is used with other lora, it is recommended to adjust it below 0.8 according to the situation. There are not many types of illustrations temporarily generated, and I hope to return some pictures (mainly due to the limitation of brain hole)

In terms of creative overview, it is that the light paintings generated by mj are too magical, and it seems that station C has never seen this variety before, so let me fill it in

The materials used include a certain book and some pictures that I have tried to shoot in light painting collections, as well as mj generated pictures to supplement human faces

The main starting word is "light painting", other words can be played freely, it seems very suitable to play with controlnet

items.description:
NOTE: ALL CHARACTERS IN THE IMAGES ARE ADULTS.

How to Use This Model

USE THEM SIMULTANEOUSLY. In this case, you need to download both koharu_bluearchive.pt and koharu_bluearchive.safetensors, then use koharu_bluearchive.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use koharu_bluearchive.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

それらを同時に使用してください。この場合、koharu_bluearchive.ptとkoharu_bluearchive.safetensorsの両方をダウンロード する必要があります。koharu_bluearchive.ptをテクスチャ反転埋め込みとして使用し、同時にkoharu_bluearchive.safetensorsをLoRAとして使用してください。

同时使用它们。在这种情况下，您需要下载koharu_bluearchive.pt和koharu_bluearchive.safetensors这两个文件，然后将koharu_bluearchive.pt用作纹理反转嵌入， 同时使用koharu_bluearchive.safetensors作为LoRA。

(Translated with ChatGPT)

The trigger word is koharu_bluearchive, and the recommended tags are masterpiece, best quality, highres, 1girl, solo, {koharu_bluearchive:1.10}, head_wings, pink_hair, twintails, wings, blush, black_wings, pink_eyes, bangs, halo, feathered_wings, hat, beret, black_headwear, low_wings, long_hair, collarbone, closed_mouth.

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Koharu Bluearchive

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is fine-tune the tags you use.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/koharu_bluearchive, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/koharu_bluearchive, which may be help to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

items.name: FurryArt
items.description:
"My main motivation to creating these models, was to make more artistic or stylised furry art."

I made four models mix using yiff-e18, zack3D(v1), BB95 Furry Mix, Fluffrock and many others.

Note: This is a Male NSFW/SFW furry focused model

however you can still produce females

* please, read all text to choose the best model 😉 *

About the models:

  1. FurryArt_noise-offset: This is my noise-offset model. This allows to produce high dynamic range images, you can use optionally CFG_Rescale_webui extensions.

  1. FurryArt_B: Similar to the previous model, but this is a no noise-offest model. Is more accurate for furry artists. Work very well with very low CFG and very high CFG scale, for this use dynamic-thresholding

  2. FurryArt_C: renders fur and hair better

    ->F. Art_C ver.2 It is an improvement of the previous model (merged with FluffyRock), more photorealistic

    EDITED: tends to have more ornamentations.

  3. FurryArt_FR: This was first FluffyRock model merged. The purpose was to create a model more easy and flexible to write prompts.

    ->F. Art_FR ver.2 It is an improvement of previous model, and is more photorealistic.

  4. FurryArt_D: This is a derivate of "FurryArt_B". I believe the other model is a finished project. So, I decided to create it from scratch.

    ->Model for soft/painting and semi photorealistic images

    • NOTE: This is not a "noise offset" model, but it seems to behave like a "noise offset". So, you can use CFG_Rescale_webui extension if you want or use this great model nLoRA to control dinamic light.

    • EDITED: Works great with very very low cfg, you can use SAG additionally

  5. FurryArt_R: Model designed to be semi photorealistic, realistic/3d, but it is possible to generate other types of art, works good with "hires.fix" or using "Refiner (you need chosse any SD1.5 model)". Can be unstable with LoRas, also a bit unstable with hands.

Recommended VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000

Edited: You can use any VAE as you want

Usefull extensions:

dynamic-thresholding to use in very high cfg scales

"Alternate Init Noise" to control colors, contrast and lighting expousure

CFG_Rescale_webui extensions to control dynamic range lighting (in offset noise models)

SAG to improve sharpness

nLoRA to control dinamic light.

  • Select your LoRA and use the triggerword

  • Make sure to change the weight if needed (by default it's :1)

  • Have Fun!

Why is my results different from yours?

  • Enable quantization in K samplers in your settings

  • Keep your prompts simple and correct

    • Tag auto complete extension to help you with your tags

    • Neg embedding have a great impact on the output of a model

    • Depending on the one you are using, results will be different.

    • I mainly use fitCorder embeddings for negative :)
